# Chrome Extension

## Structure
```
extension/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ manifest.json          # Manifest V3, version 1.1.0
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ popup/                 # popup.html, popup.css, popup.js
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ content/               # content.js (extraction), content.css
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ background/            # service-worker.js (token refresh every 55 min)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ icons/                 # icon16/48/128.png (generated from app logo PNG)
```

## Dev / Prod URL Toggle
Both `popup.js` and `service-worker.js` use a single flag to switch between local dev and production. **Never hardcode `PRODUCTION_URL` as the active URL.**

```javascript
// ‚öÝÔ∏è  BEFORE PUBLISHING: Set IS_DEV = false and fill in PRODUCTION_URL.
const IS_DEV = true;
const DEV_URL = 'http://localhost:8000';
const PRODUCTION_URL = 'https://your-applypilot-instance.com';
const BASE_URL = IS_DEV ? DEV_URL : PRODUCTION_URL;

const CONFIG = {
  API_BASE_URL: `${BASE_URL}/api/v1`,
  DASHBOARD_URL: `${BASE_URL}/dashboard`,
  APP_URL: BASE_URL,
  // ...
};
```

The URL can also be overridden at runtime via `chrome.storage.local` key `jaa_api_url` (useful during development):
```javascript
chrome.storage.local.set({ jaa_api_url: 'http://localhost:8000/api/v1' })
```

