## Icons
Icons (`icon16.png`, `icon48.png`, `icon128.png`) are generated from the app's logo PNG using Pillow:
```bash
cd /path/to/project && source venv/bin/activate
python3 -c "
from PIL import Image
src = 'path/to/logo.png'
img = Image.open(src).convert('RGBA')
for size in [16, 48, 128]:
    img.resize((size, size), Image.LANCZOS).save(f'extension/icons/icon{size}.png')
"
```

## Popup Design
The popup (`popup.html` / `popup.css`) mirrors the main app's design system exactly:
- **Same CSS variables**: `--accent-gradient`, `--bg-primary/secondary/tertiary`, `--text-*`, `--border-color`, etc.
- **Same font**: `Outfit` from Google Fonts
- **Font Awesome 6** loaded from CDN (`cdnjs.cloudflare.com`) for all icons ‚Äî no emoji
- **Header logo**: gradient rounded square (`logo-icon` div with `fas fa-rocket`) + "Apply**Pilot**" (Pilot in `var(--accent-primary)`)
- **No rounded outer corners** ‚Äî Chrome's native popup window clips them; do not add `border-radius` to `html`/`body`/`.popup-container`

### Popup sections (authenticated view)
1. Header: gradient top bar + logo + status dot
2. **Inline notification bar** (`#popupNotification`) ‚Äî hidden by default, slides in below the header on sign-in/sign-out/copy events
3. User card: gradient avatar with initials, name, email
4. Job detection row: briefcase icon + "Job detected on **{domain}**"
5. "Analyze This Job" gradient button (full width, bolt icon)
6. Hint text: "Extracts page content and sends it to AI for analysis"
7. Quick links grid (4 cols): Dashboard / Settings / Help / Logout
8. Footer: `v2.0.0` (must match `manifest.json` `version` and `popup.html` footer)

### Inline notification bar ‚Äî `#popupNotification`

Replaces the old `position: fixed` floating toast. The bar is always inside the popup frame and is never clipped by popup height changes during view transitions.

**Typography (source of truth: `extension/popup/popup.css`):** body text **14px**, **line-height ~1.45**, **max-height ~120px** with vertical scroll for long API messages (e.g. duplicate-job copy), **`align-items: flex-start`** so the icon aligns with wrapped lines; hint under the primary button (`.action-hint`) is **12px**. Do not shrink the bar back to a single-line **48px** clip ‚Äî long `RES_3002` messages must remain readable.

```html
<!-- popup.html ‚Äî inserted immediately after </header> -->
<div id="popupNotification" class="popup-notification hidden" role="alert" aria-live="polite"></div>
```

```css
/* popup.css ‚Äî illustrative; match the live file */
.popup-notification {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: 10px;
  padding: 12px 16px;
  font-size: 14px;
  line-height: 1.45;
  max-height: 120px;
  overflow-x: hidden;
  overflow-y: auto;
  transition: max-height 0.25s ease, opacity 0.25s ease, padding 0.25s ease;
}
.popup-notification > span { flex: 1; min-width: 0; }
.popup-notification.hidden { max-height: 0; padding-top: 0; padding-bottom: 0; opacity: 0; }
.popup-notification.success { background: rgba(16,185,129,.18); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(16,185,129,.35); color: #34d399; }
.popup-notification.error   { background: rgba(239,68,68,.18);  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(239,68,68,.35);  color: #f87171; }
.popup-notification.info    { background: rgba(59,130,246,.18);  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.35);  color: #60a5fa; }
```

```javascript
// popup.js ‚Äî showToast() targets the bar, not document.body
let _notifTimer = null;
function showToast(message, type = 'info') {
  const bar = document.getElementById('popupNotification');
  if (!bar) return;
  const icons = { success: 'fa-circle-check', error: 'fa-circle-xmark', info: 'fa-circle-info' };
  if (_notifTimer) { clearTimeout(_notifTimer); _notifTimer = null; }
  bar.className = `popup-notification ${type}`;
  const icon = icons[type] ?? icons.info;
  bar.innerHTML = `<i class="fas ${icon} notif-icon"></i><span>${message}</span>`;
  _notifTimer = setTimeout(() => { bar.classList.add('hidden'); _notifTimer = null; }, 3000);
}
```

**Never revert to `position: fixed` toast appended to `document.body`** ‚Äî it disappears when the popup changes height during view transitions.

### Duplicate workflow start ‚Äî `RES_3002`

If `POST .../workflow/start` returns **409** with `error_code === 'RES_3002'`, the user already has an application for that job. **`popup.js`** / **`service-worker.js`** must show an **info** (or warning-style) message via `showToast` / the same UX path ‚Äî not a generic network error. Details: `applypilot-core.mdc` (`RES_3002`).

## Content extraction (`extension/lib/extract-page-content.js`)

The popup and context menu inject **`lib/extract-page-content.js`**, then call **`window.__jaaExtractPageContent`**. One shared implementation (no duplicated logic).

- **Selection first:** if the user highlighted **‚â• 100** characters, that string is the payload (same as before on the context menu; now also applies to the popup primary button).
- **JSON-LD `JobPosting`:** parse `script[type="application/ld+json"]` for `schema.org` **JobPosting** (including `@graph`). Prefer LD when it is the full description; if the visible DOM is clearly a superset of the same text, use **DOM** to avoid stubs. For partial LD (**‚â• ~40** chars) plus DOM, **merge** (`source: json-ld+dom`). **`og:description` / meta description** can be appended when the body is still short.
- **SPA retry:** `__jaaExtractPageContentAsync` runs extraction twice with a **~500ms** gap and keeps the longer result (helps lazy-loaded job panels).
- **Site connectors:** `SITE_CONNECTOR_ROOTS` maps **hostname regex** ‚Üí extra **root selectors** (Indeed, Glassdoor, ZipRecruiter, Monster, CareerBuilder, Workday `myworkdayjobs.com`, Greenhouse, Lever, Ashby). These are merged into the candidate list before scoring.
- **Otherwise (generic DOM):** collect candidates ‚Äî `main`, `[role="main"]`, `article` (when substantial), common `job-description` / `job-details` / `posting` attribute substring selectors, plus **optional hostname hints** (e.g. detail-pane selectors on split-view job search URLs). **Score** each candidate by length, job-keyword hits, paragraph count, and penalize ‚Äúmany very short lines‚Äù (list-like). Pick the best subtree, else **`document.body`**.
- **Strip chrome** before `innerText`: includes **`aside`** / **`[role="complementary"]`** to drop sidebars. Light text cleanup (e.g. `(Verified job)` fragments).
- **Split list + detail:** exclude candidates inside **`[class*="jobs-search-results"]`** (and similar list-rail substrings); **prefer** panes matching **`jobs-search__job-details`** / **`jobs-details__main`** with enough text; strip list-rail subtrees from clones when the root is still broad (`main` / `body`). On LinkedIn split views, prefer **`jobs-search__right-rail`** / job-details wrapper and exclude **`job-card-container`** list rows.

**Context menu** (`service-worker.js`): loads the same file + runner; passes through `title` for metadata only (popup still sends **`job_text` only** to `/workflow/start`).

**Confidence + UX:** `extractPageContent` sets **`confidence`**: `high` | `medium` | `low`. After a successful analyze, **`popup.js`** may show a longer **info** toast suggesting the user **select the job description** if confidence is not high (last-mile support, not a hard error).

## Form autofill ‚Äî `extension/lib/form-autofill.js` + `POST /api/v1/extension/autofill/map`

- **Popup:** **Match Form To Profile** injects `lib/form-autofill.js`, runs async serialize (`__jaaSerializeAutofillFieldsAsync` when available ‚Äî deep-scroll for long application pages), then POSTs JSON `{ fields, page_url }` with `Authorization: Bearer`. On success, `assignments` are applied via `__jaaApplyAutofillAssignmentsWithRematchAsync` (re-scan + label rematch before apply; script re-injected as needed). User reviews and submits on the host page.
- **Server:** `api/extension_autofill.py` calls Gemini, then `_finalize_autofill_response()` merges **`api/extension_autofill_rules.py`** overlay (wins on duplicate `field_uid`; preserves `label_text` for client rematch). Same merge on Redis cache replay.
- **Deterministic rules (never mention specific job sites in user-facing copy):** name/email/phone, country vs city location, work authorization, visa sponsorship, acknowledgements, education degree/discipline/school, website/portfolio, consent checkboxes, NYC commute screening, etc. Profile fields: `work_authorization`, `requires_visa_sponsorship`, `country`, education JSONB, stored resume via `utils/user_resume_storage.py`.
- **Client apply paths:** `applyYesNoComboboxAsync` (exact Yes/No only), `applyAcknowledgementComboboxAsync` (long ‚ÄúYes, I acknowledge‚Ä¶‚Äù options), `applyLocationCityComboboxAsync`, education block expand + sort order, `assignmentUidStillValid` / `findFieldUidForAssignment` to avoid cross-wiring screening UIDs.
- **MVP scope:** main `document` only (no iframes/shadow roots). Popup does not send **`extras`**; endpoint still accepts optional **`extras`** for other clients.
- **Errors:** `CFG_6001` ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí AI Setup. **403** ‚Üí complete profile setup (work authorization required for extension map).
- **Docs:** `extension/README.md`, `USER_GUIDE.md` Chrome Extension section, `CHANGELOG.md` [Unreleased], Help FAQ ‚Äî keep user-facing text generic (‚Äúany job site‚Äù, ‚Äúapplication forms‚Äù), no third-party job board names.

## Submitting to Backend

The extension POSTs `FormData` with only `job_text` ‚Äî never `detected_title` or `detected_company`:

```javascript
const formData = new FormData();
formData.append('job_text', extractedText);
// Do NOT send detected_title / detected_company ‚Äî page titles are unreliable
// (e.g. a noisy browser tab title). The dashboard shows skeleton shimmers while the
// Job Analyzer extracts the correct title and company from the job text.

const response = await fetch(`${CONFIG.API_BASE_URL}/workflow/start`, {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Authorization': `Bearer ${state.token}` },
    body: formData
});
```

### Backend: `detected_title` / `detected_company` Form params

`POST /api/v1/workflow/start` accepts two optional `Form` fields (retained for non-extension paths):

```python
detected_title_form:   Optional[str] = Form(None, alias="detected_title")
detected_company_form: Optional[str] = Form(None, alias="detected_company")
```

When omitted (the extension path), `job_title` and `company_name` are `null` at creation. The dashboard card shows skeleton shimmers (`status === 'processing'`, no title/company). The Job Analyzer agent populates both fields with AI-extracted values ~4 s into the workflow.

